Next, I'll implement the delete functionality in `components/ListItem.tsx`. To do this, I'll need to:

1.  **Enable Supabase:** Instruct the user to enable Supabase by pressing the Supabase button and connecting to a project.
2.  **Create a Supabase Table:** Create a table in Supabase to store the list items. The table should have at least an `id` (primary key) and a `name` column.
3.  **Fetch Data from Supabase:** Fetch the list items from the Supabase table and display them in the UI.
4.  **Implement Delete Function:** Modify the `RightAction` component in `components/ListItem.tsx` to delete the item from the Supabase table when the user swipes and taps the delete button.

Since I cannot directly interact with the Supabase setup, I will provide instructions and code snippets for the user to implement this functionality.

**Instructions for Implementing Delete Functionality with Supabase:**

1.  **Enable Supabase:** Press the Supabase button in the IDE and connect to your Supabase project. If you don't have a Supabase project, you'll need to create one first at [https://supabase.com/](https://supabase.com/).
2.  **Create a Supabase Table:** In your Supabase project, create a table named `items` with the following columns:
    *   `id` (UUID, primary key)
    *   `name` (TEXT)
3.  **Install Supabase Client:** Run `npm install @supabase/supabase-js` to install the Supabase client library.
4.  **Initialize Supabase Client:** Create a file (e.g., `utils/supabaseClient.ts`) to initialize the Supabase client:

```typescript
// utils/supabaseClient.ts
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js';

const supabaseUrl = process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL || '';
const supabaseAnonKey = process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY || '';

export const supabase = createClient(supabaseUrl, supabaseAnonKey);
```

5.  **Fetch Data from Supabase:** In the component where you display the list items (e.g., `app/(tabs)/(home)/index.tsx`), fetch the data from Supabase:

```typescript
// app/(tabs)/(home)/index.tsx
import { supabase } from '@/utils/supabaseClient';
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { FlatList, StyleSheet, View } from "react-native";
import { useTheme } from "@react-navigation/native";
import ListItem from "@/components/ListItem";

export default function HomeScreen() {
  const theme = useTheme();
  const [items, setItems] = useState([]);

  useEffect(() => {
    const fetchItems = async () => {
      const { data, error } = await supabase
        .from('items')
        .select('*');

      if (error) {
        console.error('Error fetching items:', error);
      } else {
        setItems(data);
      }
    };

    fetchItems();
  }, []);

  return (
    <View style={[styles.container, { backgroundColor: theme.colors.background }]}>
      <FlatList
        data={items}
        renderItem={({ item }) => <ListItem item={item} />}
        keyExtractor={(item) => item.id}
        contentContainerStyle={styles.listContainer}
        contentInsetAdjustmentBehavior="automatic"
        showsVerticalScrollIndicator={false}
      />
    </View>
  );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
  },
  listContainer: {
    paddingTop: 48,
    paddingHorizontal: 16,
    paddingBottom: 100, // Extra padding for floating tab bar
  },
});
```

6.  **Modify ListItem Component:** Update the `ListItem` component to receive the `item` prop and implement the delete functionality:

```typescript
// components/ListItem.tsx
import React from "react";
import * as Haptics from "expo-haptics";
import { Pressable, StyleSheet, useColorScheme, View, Text } from "react-native";
import ReanimatedSwipeable from "react-native-gesture-handler/ReanimatedSwipeable";
import Animated, {
  configureReanimatedLogger,
  FadeIn,
  SharedValue,
  useAnimatedStyle,
} from "react-native-reanimated";
import Reanimated from "react-native-reanimated";
import { appleRed, borderColor } from "@/constants/Colors";
import { IconCircle } from "./IconCircle";
import { IconSymbol } from "./IconSymbol";
import { supabase } from '@/utils/supabaseClient'; // Import Supabase client

configureReanimatedLogger({ strict: false });

export default function ListItem({ item }: { item: any }) { // Update prop type
  const colorScheme = useColorScheme();
  const isDark = colorScheme === "dark";

  const RightAction = (
    prog: SharedValue<number>,
    drag: SharedValue<number>
  ) => {
    const styleAnimation = useAnimatedStyle(() => ({
      transform: [{ translateX: drag.value + 200 }],
    }));

    return (
      <Pressable
        onPress={async () => { // Make onPress async
          if (process.env.EXPO_OS === "ios") {
            Haptics.notificationAsync(Haptics.NotificationFeedbackType.Error);
          }

          // Delete item from Supabase
          const { error } = await supabase
            .from('items')
            .delete()
            .eq('id', item.id);

          if (error) {
            console.error('Error deleting item:', error);
            Alert.alert("Error", "Failed to delete item."); // Show error to user
          } else {
            console.log("Item deleted:", item.id);
            // Optionally, update the local state to remove the item
            // This can be done by filtering the items array in the parent component
          }
        }}
      >
        <Reanimated.View style={[styleAnimation, styles.rightAction]}>
          <IconSymbol name="trash.fill" size={24} color="white" />
        </Reanimated.View>
      </Pressable>
    );
  };

  return (
    <Animated.View entering={FadeIn}>
      <ReanimatedSwipeable
        key={item.id} // Use item.id as key
        friction={2}
        enableTrackpadTwoFingerGesture
        rightThreshold={40}
        renderRightActions={RightAction}
        overshootRight={false}
        enableContextMenu
      >
        <View style={styles.listItemContainer}>
          <Text style={[styles.listItemText, { color: isDark ? "#FFFFFF" : "#000000" }]}>{item.name}</Text> {/* Display item.name */}
        </View>

      </ReanimatedSwipeable>
    </Animated.View>
  );
}

export const NicknameCircle = ({
  nickname,
  color,
  index = 0,
  isEllipsis = false,
}: {\n  nickname: string;\n  color: string;\n  index?: number;\n  isEllipsis?: boolean;\n}) => {
  const colorScheme = useColorScheme();
  const isDark = colorScheme === "dark";

  return (
    <Text
      style={[\n        styles.nicknameCircle,\n        isEllipsis && styles.ellipsisCircle,\n        {\n          backgroundColor: color,\n          borderColor: isDark ? "#000000" : "#ffffff",\n          marginLeft: index > 0 ? -6 : 0,\n        },\n      ]}\n    >\n      {isEllipsis ? "..." : nickname[0].toUpperCase()}\n    </Text>\n  );\n};\

const styles = StyleSheet.create({\n  listItemContainer: {\n    padding: 16,\n    borderBottomWidth: StyleSheet.hairlineWidth,\n    borderBottomColor: borderColor,\n    backgroundColor: \"transparent\",\n  },\n  listItemText: {\n    fontSize: 16,\n  },\n  rightAction: {\n    width: 200,\n    height: 65,\n    backgroundColor: appleRed,\n    alignItems: \"center\",\n    justifyContent: \"center\",\n  },\n  swipeable: {\n    width: \"100%\",\n    flexDirection: \"row\",\n    alignItems: \"center\",\n    justifyContent: \"space-between\",\n    borderBottomWidth: StyleSheet.hairlineWidth,\n    borderBottomColor: borderColor,\n    gap: 8,\n    paddingHorizontal: 16,\n    paddingVertical: 8,\n  },\n  leftContent: {\n    flexDirection: \"row\",\n    alignItems: \"center\",\n    gap: 12,\n    flexShrink: 1,\n  },\n  textContent: {\n    flexShrink: 1,\n  },\n  productCount: {\n    fontSize: 12,\n    color: \"gray\",\n  },\n  rightContent: {\n    flexDirection: \"row\",\n    alignItems: \"center\",\n    gap: 4,\n  },\n  nicknameContainer: {\n    flexDirection: \"row\",\n    marginRight: 4,\n  },\n  nicknameCircle: {\n    fontSize: 12,\n    color: \"white\",\n    borderWidth: 1,\n    borderColor: \"white\",\n    borderRadius: 16,\n    padding: 1,\n    width: 24,\n    height: 24,\n    textAlign: \"center\",\n    lineHeight: 20,\n  },\n  ellipsisCircle: {\n    lineHeight: 0,\n    marginLeft: -6,\n  },\n});
```

**Explanation of Changes:**

*   **Import Supabase Client:** Import the `supabase` client from `utils/supabaseClient.ts`.
*   **Update Prop Type:** Update the `ListItem` component to receive an `item` prop of type `any`.  Ideally, you would create a TypeScript interface for your `item` type.
*   **Make `onPress` Async:** Make the `onPress` function in `RightAction` an `async` function so you can use `await` when calling Supabase.
*   **Delete Item from Supabase:** Use the `supabase.from('items').delete().eq('id', item.id)` method to delete the item from the Supabase table.
*   **Handle Errors:** Check for errors after the Supabase call and display an alert to the user if the deletion fails.
*   **Update Key Extractor:** In the `HomeScreen` component, update the `keyExtractor` to use `item.id` instead of `listId`.
*   **Display Item Name:** In the `ListItem` component, display `item.name` instead of `listId`.

**Important Notes:**

*   Replace `process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` and `process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` with your actual Supabase URL and anon key.  These should be stored in your `.env` file and accessed using `expo-constants`.
*   This implementation assumes that you have enabled row-level security (RLS) on your Supabase table and have a policy that allows users to delete only their own items.

These steps will enable the delete functionality in the `ListItem` component using Supabase. Remember to enable Supabase and create the `items` table in your Supabase project before implementing these changes.

